-- U.K. Shopping Centers Attract Foreign Investors, Telegraph Says
-- B y   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 2012-03-11T10:35:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/u-k-shopping-centers-attract-foreign-investors-telegraph-says.html
Two U.K. shopping centers are
attracting investors from Norway, Singapore and  Abu Dhabi , the
Sunday Telegraph said, citing people familiar with the deals.  Festival Place shopping center in Basingstoke may sell for
as much as 300 million pounds ($470 million) with bidding due to
close March 16, the newspaper said. A fifty percent stake in
Meadowhall in Sheffield, worth about 800 million pounds, may be
sold within the next two weeks, the newspaper said.  Interested parties include Norges Bank  Investment
Management (WAC) , Government of Singapore Investment Corp. and the Abu
Dhabi Investment Authority, the Sunday Telegraph reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
